description.0: Captain America is forced to face his biggest battle in months when AIM rears its head. The future of mankind is in the balance!
description.1: May Parker's secret super hero identity is finally revealed to her parents and they're not happy about it. Unfortunately, she's got deadlier things to worry about.
description.2: Xavier is found by the X-Men...but why is he leading the Brotherhood of Mutants?
description.5: A Kree-sized crisis hits Marvel's First Family! Ronan the Accuser has come to Earth, and it is the Fantastic Four that stand accused!
description.9: Warlock must gain control of Drax's stolen Nega-Bands if he wants to save the galaxy from being sucked into the Negative Zone!
description.11: The new Avengers are hiring! And Shannon Carter, also known as American Dream, may be perfect for the job!
description.12: Members of X-Force find themselves kidnapped by Pandemonia and mindcontrolled to kidnap the rest of the group. Can the team defeat the self-styled Queen of Chaos?
description.13: X-Force learns of a town subject to experimentation. What has happened to this town and is X-Force to late to help?
description.15: Femme fatale Baroness puts all her vampire players in place to pull off her next sinister scheme...and this one involves Kenneth Crichton, grandson of the original Union Jack!
description.17: Who infected the Fantastic Four? The Fantastic Four must find out who infected them, and they’ll need all the magical help they can get!
description.18: Collects Spider-Man's Tangled Web (2001) #7-12.  This critically-acclaimed collection features the Bruce Jones and Lee Weeks's  "Gentlemen's Agreement", Kaare Andrews's "Ray of Light", and Darwyn Cooke's "Open All Night": three stories of ordinary people whose lives are forever changed by Spider-Man!
description.19: Collects Tales To Astonish #76, Tales Of Suspense #88 - #91, Captain Marvel #17, Daredevil #146, Marvel Premiere #1 And #15, What If? #3 And #24, Amazing Spider-Man #99 And #123, Marvel Comics Presents #116.  A lifetime retrospective of the legend's greatest work for the House of Ideas!   Joining the immortal Stan Lee, Jack Kirby, Steve Ditko and John Romita in the annals of The House's history is one of the industry's most gifted artists: Gil Kane! With his fluid pencils, Kane brought a loving familiarity to Mighty Marvel's most popular characters in a body of work reprinted for fans new and old alike!
description.20: Cable heads to Doctor Doom’s sovereign nation of Latveria to rescue the X-Man from Stryfe!
description.21: With Jabba the Hutt dead, a swarm of greedy Hutt relatives descend on Tatooine ready to claim their piece of Jabba's vast criminal empire. But Big Gizz and Spiker, Jabba's swoop-riding thugs, have their own agenda for a hidden ship full of Jabba's most precious art treasures. Unfortunately, the ship is protected with a security program modeled on Jabba himself!
description.24: Ki-Adi-Mundi'is a'Jedi Knight'of formidable power and influence, but not on his own homeworld of'Cerea. Most of the planet's citizens are happy to continue their low-tech lives of simplicity, isolated from the'Republic, but a new generation of'Cereans'crave'speeder bikes'and'starships, and are prepared to fight their elders for them! How can a'Jedi'take up arms against his own children?
description.25: Kyp Durron'arrives on the mining'world'of'Corbos'only to find the entire colony destroyed. There are no signs of life but Kyp can still hear the psychic outcries of the colonists. He is drawn toward the'Leviathan'of Corbos, a beast that he finds has devoured the colonists, and yet trapped their minds and spirits. And it's up to Kyp to defeat the Leviathan on his own!
description.26: Fed up with being hunted by her enemies,'Mara Jade'decides it's time to become the hunter. First on her payback list? The evil'Dequc,'Black Nebula crime lord, the man who survived her final assignment for the'Emperor! Now, Mara must infiltrate his hidden base, take him down, and escape! Could she finally be in over her head?
description.33: As the death toll rises, so do the stakes for the future of the'Empire. Who is committing these assassinations of'Interim Council'members and who within the Empire has the most to gain? Why has'Mirith Sinn'abandoned the'New Republic'to fulfill a personal vendetta? And how does'Kir Kanos'fit into this jigsaw puzzle of intrigue?
description.36: Doctor Strange summons the Hulk and the Sub-Mariner to combat the A-Next crew! It's the original DEFENDERS against the new AVENGERS!
description.37: Sam is caught between warring factions of super-powered Deviants! Can this former New Mutant win against the New Deviants?! Only with the aid of X-Force!
description.40: Failing actor Joey Chapman becomes the protector of Great Britain! As Union Jack, Joey will have to embrace decades-long traditions while risking life and limb to stem the tide of evil. And the latest threat to endanger England? Try a roving band of vampires intent on stealing an ancient relic of vast power! Former Invader Spitfire guest-stars!
description.41: If you can't beat 'em, join 'em, right? And if you won't join 'em, they'll force you to! Can the Hulk escape the clutches of the murderous Circus of Crime?
description.42: A group of young Inhumans embark on the greatest journey of their lives. It's time for Terrigenesis!
description.43: J2 vs. the Incredible Hulk! Some serious damage is incurred in a showdown between Marvel's heaviest hitters. Zane flexes his heroism by saving Talia and Montana from a sinister Halloween gag!
description.45: Nightmare is now after Sharon Carter, and Captain America must come to her rescue!
description.46: Spider-Girl and The Fantastic Five join forces to defeat a robber at the Fantastic Five museum.
description.47: The Hunt for Xavier is on and the X-Men split up to follow up on clues as to where their mentor is now.
description.48: Wolverine goes searching for a man involved in a domestic abuse case against a wife and daughter.
description.50: Sue, Johnny, and Ben are forced to fight...themselves!? Mind-swapped with the Crucible's lackeys, can even the timely escape of Reed Richards help them become themselves again?
description.51: Tony's still recuperating, but the threats against Iron Man persist. Why is War Machine attacking Stark? And what unkind words will Warbird have for Iron Man?
description.53: When M.O.D.O.K. returns, Iron Man and Captain America assemble to take down the big-headed villain. Plus, Iron Man reveals a big secret to those closest to him.
description.56: The true killer is revealed in a shocking twist! Adam Warlock and his team are shocked, but have to be prepared to fight for their very lives!
description.64: Viper sends Wolverine out on a mission to find the source of a deadly virus.
description.65: Nomi Sunrider travels to Rhen Var to find her daughter training with Ulic Qel-Droma. She tries to take Vima away but sees that she needs to make her own decisions. Sylvar also arrives on Rhen Var seeking to kill Ulic for killing her mate. But while fighting Ulic she comes to understand that she needs to move beyond her anger over her mate's death.
description.67: After receiving a distress call,'Kyp Durron'and'Dorsk 82'come to'Corbos, only to find they are too late. The colony is destroyed leaving only evidence of a slaughter...and a'monster! Kyp slips away at night to track down the hideous beast. When Dorsk 82 awakens to find him gone, he immediately summons help, but before they can arrive, Kyp, alone, finds the monster.
description.68: Following the death of'Carnor Jax'in the first'Crimson Empire'series, the Empire'suddenly finds itself devoid of a strong leader. The'Interim Councilis assembled to manage the affairs of the Empire until a new emperor can take the throne, yet something is amiss. Assassinations begin to whittle down the numbers of the council, causing panic and suspicion. Increased raids on otherwise "safe"'Rebel'trade routes arouse concern within the'New Republic. And just where, exactly, has'Kir Kanos'gone?
description.75: After'the death'of'Emperor'Palpatine,'Mara Jade'escapes from'Imperial Center'and throws herself headlong into the underground of the'Empire's underworld. Though her master is dead, Jade must complete her final mission, even if it costs her life!
description.78: Adam Warlock is back! And after he discovers a longtime friend has been murdered by Drax the Destroyer, Adam gathers his old teammates Gamora and Pip the Troll to find Drax – and get vengeance!
description.79: There isn't much cooler than Daredevil flying high above the Hell's Kitchen skyline with nothing but his trusty billy club in hand. On this cover, Marvel Editor-in-Chief Joe Quesada shows us all why Matt Murdock is known as The Man Without Fear.
description.80: This strange new group of Mighty Avengers have finally found their first arch nemesis!
description.81: Cannonball returns home to Kentucky for some peaceful contemplation, but things get complicated for Sam when he stumbles across mutants who are being hunted!
description.82: Celebrating the 25th anniversary of Secret Wars! What if Marvel's heroes never escaped the Beyonder's Battleworld?! Trapped in a world unfamiliar, super humans like Captain America, Rogue, She-Hulk and Hawkeye, are forced to settle into new lives and roles!
description.85: RETURN OF THE GREEN GOBLIN! Norman Osborn prepares to reincarnate himself as the Green Goblin once again as Spider-man continues to fight Molten Man.
description.88: While the Avengers battle the Mandarin's 'Dragon of Heaven', a down for the count Iron Man stares down his adversary. Tony Stark's never been this helpless against the Mandarin- will his Avenging teammates pull off a rescue...or will Shellhead secure his own escape?
description.89: The Hulk's search for answers leads him to Las Vegas - straight into the arms of the Circus of Crime! Step right up, as the Hulk throws down with the Circus in the greatest show on Earth!
description.90: Trouble is brewing in the city of Attilan and King Black Bolt isn't helping matters.
description.91: Zane's super hero career is off to a rollicking start- J2's been admitted to the Avengers! But there's trouble on the home front! Zane's mom is intent on exposing J2's civilian identity, and high school bully Miller won't let Zane catch a break. Plus, the Uncanny X-People!
description.95: The extreme patriots are going homicidal... What does this mean for the Cap?
description.96: Spider-Girl comes face-to-face with Crazy Eight on her journey to finding out if crime fighting is the life for her.
description.97: Black Tom Cassidy requests the help of Storm and Kitty to retrieve the Cytorrak Gem for a now depowered Juggernaut. Things get interesting when Gambit comes out of the woodwork to steal the gem for his own personal gain.
description.98: Wolverine and his new ally are forced to fight, or flee, the Wendigo!

3.text: THE HUNT FOR XAVIER PART 4 Cerebrite Alpha launches a psychic attack against the team, preying on personal weaknesses. Humanity awaits 'final programming'. Enter Cerebro Prime.

4.text: The avenging Hawkeye sets a plan in motion to take down the T-bolts.  Hercules returns for revenge against Atlas. A supersized battle between two awesome, god-like beings!

6.text: The prelude to Gambit's ongoing series! Gambit’s been hired out by the mysterious New Son to collect a ‘sigil’ from the High Evolutionary’s base in the Savage Land. Little does Gambit know…the ‘sigil’ is a human being!

7.text: The Heroes for Hire disband following their perilous Madripoor mission!

8.text: Two days after being thawed out, Cap goes out in Brooklyn with Tony Stark. Iron Man notices something a bit off about Steve Rogers…

9.text: Warlock must gain control of Drax's stolen Nega-Bands if he wants to save the galaxy from being sucked into the Negative Zone!

10.text: Foggy Nelson has been set up! After being accused of killing a client, his mother cuts him loose from the firm. Meanwhile, Daredevil is abducted and then confronted by an angelic stranger looking for the missing child.

Foggy Nelson has been set up! After being accused of killing a client, his mother cuts him loose from the firm. Meanwhile, Daredevil is abducted and then confronted by an angelic stranger looking for the missing child.

12.text: Members of X-Force find themselves kidnapped by Pandemonia and mindcontrolled to kidnap the rest of the group. Can the team defeat the self-styled Queen of Chaos?

14.text: It’s a family affair (of sorts) as Cable, Nate, Madelyne Pryor and Stryfe duke it out for the sake of all mutants! This is the end-of-the-line, explosive conclusion to the X-Man/Cable crossover!

18.text: Today's hottest writers and artists take a hard look at the shadow Spider-Man casts over his friendly neighborhood and the people who live in it.

19.text: The late Gil Kane was a true comic-book legend, illustrating nearly every major Marvel super hero during a career that spanned more than 40 years. His innovative figure work, emotionally charged characters and action-packed fight scenes have influenced hundreds of today's top illustrators.

20.text: Cable heads to Doctor Doom’s sovereign nation of Latveria to rescue the X-Man from Stryfe!

22.text: Spidey joins the Fantastic Four! Plus, an all-out brawl with Marvel's infamous master of disguise, the Chameleon!

27.text: This is it! The long-awaited battle between Deadpool and Tiamat begins here!

28.text: Mild-mannered Songbird taps into her inner Screaming Mimi with berserker rage. What has caused this sudden shift for the songstress? The Thunderbolts reel as one of their own flies off the handle, and into the cuckoo’s nest!

30.text: Wanda has been captured by the Unliving Legion! Meanwhile, the Grim Reaper casts a magic force wall around Central Park and the Avengers. Can Wanda free herself in time to aid her teammates?

32.text: A misunderstanding between Thor and Hercules leads to a divine altercation! Can Hercules come to his senses in time to help Thor?

35.text: As Matt begins to investigate his recent forced adoption of the so-called Messiah, new evidence comes to light. The child Matt has been made caretaker of is not the Messiah, but rather the Anti-Christ! Plus, Karen Page returns.

As Matt begins to investigate his recent forced adoption of the so-called Messiah, new evidence comes to light. The child Matt has been made caretaker of is not the Messiah, but rather the Anti-Christ! Plus, Karen Page returns.

38.text: It’s a Cable/X-Man crossover! Blaquesmith believes that Nate Grey will be the perfect savior in the wake of an imminent threat that could spell extinction for mutantkind.

39.text: Stryfe has arrived and he’s far too powerful a menace for X-Man to face alone! The Cable (1993) crossover continues!

44.text: Everett Ross awaits Black Panther’s return, but he's not alone! The demon Mephisto wants to offer his terrible company too! Meanwhile, Black Panther breaks up gangs while hunting for a cold-blooded killer.

49.text: THE HUNT FOR XAVIER PART 2 Where is the X-Men's leader and mentor? The team goes searching for answers in an elusive monastery, and encounters a new Alpha-class mutant!

52.text: Prepare for John Byrne's exciting revamp of the Spidey mythos!

54.text: A mystery in Madripoor leads the H4H to investigate a pirated talisman!

55.text: With the Human Torch back to his right self, he, Cap and Namor battle the Firebrand Squadron in Atlantis.

56.text: The true killer is revealed in a shocking twist! Adam Warlock and his team are shocked, but have to be prepared to fight for their very lives!

58.text: When the Blackbird crashes in the Canadian wilderness, The Six are overrun by The Pack - savage versions of Wolverine, Sabretooth and Wildchild!

59.text: Makkari of the Eternals joins the Monster Hunters to defeat Kro, Gigantus of the Deep, and the horrifying Tricephalous!

60.text: Featuring Morbius, the Living Vampire! Blade must take on an occult cult on the orders of his new (and mysterious) client!

61.text: As the demon’s identity comes to light, Frank Castle realizes that the Stalkers are foes he has faced before. Daimon Hellstrom guest-stars!

62.text: Avengers from throughout history are brought together to stop a time-war between Kang the Conqueror and Immortus!
Avengers from throughout history are brought together to stop a time-war between Kang the Conqueror and Immortus!

63.text: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 4 Nick Fury and his Howling Commandos make an electrifying appearance in the conclusion to Nemesis Contract! Will Cable be able to restore his trust in S.H.I.E.L.D.? Cable and Nick Fury unite forces in a team-up unlike any you’ve seen before!

66.text: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 3 What is on S.H.I.E.L.D.’s agenda when it comes to Cable? And will the peacekeeping task force make their motives known? A surprising twist will leave Cable questioning who, if anyone, he should trust.

69.text: Wanda delves into her past to learn how to fully resurrect Wonder Man. Meanwhile, at the Avengers Parade, the proceedings are interrupted by the Grim Reaper and the Legion of the Unliving.

71.text: Trouble is brewing at the former site of the golden city of Asgard! Meanwhile, on the plane of Midgard, Thor's hammer continues to malfunction!

72.text: Cable vs. Deadpool. The warrior from tomorrow takes on the merc with a mouth.

73.text: DECISIONS PART 1 The Thunderbolts thought they were the Masters of Evil…until a new super powered team crashes the scene! The Thunderbolts do battle with the new Masters of Evil, and the aftermath is devastation. The turning point issue that sets the stage for Avengers vs. Thunderbolts!

76.text: The Absorbing Man and Titania wreak havoc on Luke and She-Hulk's first date!

77.text: Cap escapes his imprisonment in Atlantis and discovers dozens of Prisoners of War being used in Nazi experiments!

78.text: Adam Warlock is back! And after he discovers a longtime friend has been murdered by Drax the Destroyer, Adam gathers his old teammates Gamora and Pip the Troll to find Drax – and get vengeance!

79.text: Karen Page, Matt Murdock's old flame, has been gone now for sixth months. Life goes on for Matt, until he receives a very special package. A young girl has brought a child to Murdock, claiming it to be the Messiah, and leaves the child in his care...

Karen Page, Matt Murdock's old flame, has been gone now for sixth months. Life goes on for Matt, until he receives a very special package. A young girl has brought a child to Murdock, claiming it to be the Messiah, and leaves the child in his care...

There isn't much cooler than Daredevil flying high above the Hell's Kitchen skyline with nothing but his trusty billy club in hand.  On this cover, Marvel Editor-in-Chief Joe Quesada shows us all why Matt Murdock is known as The Man Without Fear.

83.text: Re-presenting the formation of the Avengers, the revival of Captain America, enemies such as the Sub-Mariner, and Kang the Conqueror.

86.text: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 2 Introducing Agent 18, Jack Truman! Irene Merryweather and Blaquesmith become concerned for Cable after witnessing Agent 18’s incursion in Hell’s Kitchen. Why does Jack Truman want Cable dead? And to what lengths will he go to ensure a successful mission?

87.text: Quicksilver has a conversation with his subconscious, or perhaps an alternate version of his future self. In this issue, secrets are revealed about Quicksilver’s dark nature.  A can’t-miss read for any fan of Marvel’s swiftest mutant!

92.text: This is it. A souped up Green Goblin unleashes vengeance on Spider-Man.

93.text: Mister Fantastic saves Aunt May from Osborn’s doomsday device.

94.text: T’Challa allows refugees from a border skirmish into Wakanda, spurring civil unrest! Black Panther must leave it all behind to travel to New York City! There’s a Tomorrow Fund scandal that needs investigating!

99.text: Gambit returns to the X-Mansion, much to the chagrin of certain teammates. While trying to make peace in Boston, Rogue and Gambit fall under violent attack from the ‘Goddess’ Kali! Will Gambit ever admit his love for Rogue? He may not be able to, especially if the ‘Green Mist' kills him first!
